               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17600910-3-person51">
                  Mary 
                  Flight 
               <interp inst="t17600910-3-person51" type="surname" value="Flight"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17600910-3-person51" type="given" value="Mary"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17600910-3-person51" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . My sister Ann is a <rs id="t17600910-3-viclabel15" type="occupation">milliner</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17600910-3-victim46 t17600910-3-viclabel15"></join>, I live with her in Cornhill; we had lost things several times, and we suspected the prisoner.</p>
               <p>Q. What is he?</p>
               <p>M. Flight. He is <rs id="t17600910-3-deflabel16" type="occupation">a ticket-porter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17600910-3-defend44 t17600910-3-deflabel16"></join>, he us'd to shut up the shop; we laid things to catch him, the piece of ribbon was one; when they were gone we took him up, and he delivered up the key of his room, and we went and searched, and found the things mentioned in the indictment (mentioning them by name) (produc'd in court, and depos'd to) as part her sisters and part her own, and the handkerchief as the property of Mr. Macleshan.</p>
               <p>Q. Where were the things taken from?</p>
               <p>M. Flight. They were taken from out of the shop.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="176009100003"></xptr>
            
                  <persName id="t17600910-3-person52">
                  Peter 
                  Macleshan 
               <interp inst="t17600910-3-person52" type="surname" value="Macleshan"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17600910-3-person52" type="given" value="Peter"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17600910-3-person52" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I belong to the sea, I had some India soap which was missing, it was found at the prisoner's house; I am certain it was my property, there is no such soap in the country; I heard the prisoner charg'd with taking the things mentioned, and he own'd he did.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>I have some witnesses to my character; I bear a great character, and I believe very justly.</p>
               <p>For the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17600910-3-person53">
                  David 
                  Solomon 
               <interp inst="t17600910-3-person53" type="surname" value="Solomon"></interp>
