                     <interp inst="t17600910-3-person53" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I have known the prisoner 10 or 11 years.</p>
               <p>Q. What is his character?</p>
               <p>Solomon, He bears a very good character, he always was a good man.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17600910-3-person54">
                  John 
                  Hubbard 
               <interp inst="t17600910-3-person54" type="surname" value="Hubbard"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17600910-3-person54" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17600910-3-person54" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I have known him 9 or 10 years, I always took him to be a very honest man; I found him to be so, he has gone with a great many jobbs for me, and always behav'd very just.</p>
               <p>Mr. Wallis. I have known him 7 or 8 years.</p>
               <p>Q. What is his general character?</p>
               <p>Wallis. It is that of an honest man; I have trusted him with several things.</p>
               <p>Mr. North. I have known him about 3 years, he bore a good character, that of an honest man.</p>
               <p>Mr. Parker. I have known him 30 years, or upwards; he always bore a good character.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17600910-3-person55">
